A chieftain of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP), Hon Hellen Taiwo-Adebakin has rejoiced with Nigerians for witnessing the New Year 2022.. Adebakin, in her New Year Message entitled: ” 2022: Our Year of Hope and Redemption”  enjoined Nigerians to always show appreciation to God for keeping them alive in spite of the security and economic facing our dear country. The Secretary of the former and serving ex-officio members of the PDP also urged to Nigerians to put all failures and disappointments on the path of government at the centre behind them and approach the new year with new zeal and zest. Hon. Adebakin Hails Silverbird At 20 Adebakin Greets PDP National Chairman, Iyorchia Ayu On His… ” This new year 2022  will be good for all Nigerians. May every day of this year brings favour and blessing to every household in this country. Our testimonies shall be big  and we shall have many things to celebrate  on a daily basis” Adebakin While urging them not to lose hope yet, Adebakin promised that the PDP is prepared to return Nigeria to the path of greatness as soon as it attains power in 2023. ” I want to use this occasion to congratulate Nigerians on the new year 2022 celebrations. The previous year 2021 had been a year of multiple trials occasioned by the twin effect of security and economic challenges. We must give thanks and glory to God Almighty for seeing us through despite all odds. “While we pray for the divine intervention on the issues confronting our dear country, I want to also admonish Nigerians to keep faith with the PDP ahead of the all-important 2023 Presidential election. Help is certainly is on the way and it is my belief that the PDP will deliver Nigeria from her present mess.